# Cloudflare Pages serves these headers alongside every matching response.
# Format: path on first line, then `  Header-Name: value` (2-space indent).
# `! Header-Name` removes a header that the platform would otherwise inject.

# Allow Sanity Studio's Presentation tool to embed the marketing site in an
# iframe. By default Cloudflare Pages sends X-Frame-Options: SAMEORIGIN, which
# breaks click-to-edit. Drop X-Frame-Options entirely and use the modern
# CSP frame-ancestors directive — same protection, but explicitly whitelists
# the deployed Studio + the wildcard *.sanity.studio host so a future Studio
# rename (e.g. previewing a non-prod deploy) doesn't lock the editor out.
/*
  ! X-Frame-Options
  Content-Security-Policy: frame-ancestors 'self' https://team-cms.sanity.studio https://*.sanity.studio https://*.sanity.io
